						               													<description>The predators face off in a night scene where the most agile and fastest survives. Jaguars hunt alligators, curiy&amp;uacute;, owls and toads, while spider web traps and the smell of skunks turn the game into chaos.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Includes 2 game modes: Hunting on the Island and Gathering Herds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hunting on the Island&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With the agility of predators and knowledge of the species, protect the weakest animal on the island and take all the cards. You have to be very attentive, the fastest hunter wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deal all cards among players, who will leave them in a face-down pile. At the same time, all players reveal their first card. The first player to cover the weakest animal on the food chain and shout its name, wins the round and take all cards. There are also some special actions cards that could change conditions for the round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When all cards were played, the player with the most cards, wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gathering Herds&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To survive on the island, cunning and agility are essential. Group the animals by species and use all your speed to win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deal 5 to 7 cards to each player (according to the number of players). Leave the rest of the cards in a face-down deck in the middle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dealer signals the start, and each player, at the same time, can:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Put down a pair of equal cards.&amp;#10;     Put down a card equal to a pair another player put down.&amp;#10;     Take cards from the middle deck to form pairs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player is out of cards, the round finishes. Each player gets 1 point per card left in their hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the fifth round, the game ends and the lowest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
